ia convex demographic parity sets)—by instantiating multiple coordinated DDOs operating in parallel. We prove that under bounded gradient variance and uniform Slater conditions, DACG converges almost surely to a point satisfying both optimality and global constraints. Empirically, this enables stable training of deep architectures far beyond the NTK regime (validating Paper 1's expressivity condition dynamically) while achieving superior generalization and safety properties. Applications include certified adversarial robustness in Vision Transformers, fair representation learning in tabular models, and energy-constrained inference in mobile nets via rank-bounded updates. By integrating ideas from differentiable optimization, structured prediction, and constrained ML, DACG offers a scalable, theoretically sound pathway to trustworthy deep learning with built-in convex governance.",
